  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "`shap.explainers._linear.LinearExplainer` always uses `shap.maskers.Independent` regardless of  the value of `feature_perturbation` in the constructor.\r\n\r\n## Minimal Example\r\n\r\n```python\r\nimport shap\r\nimport sklearn\r\n\r\nX, y = shap.datasets.boston()\r\nmodel = sklearn.linear_model.LinearRegression()\r\nmodel.fit(X, y)\r\n\r\ninterventional = shap.explainers.Linear(model, X, feature_perturbation=\"interventional\")\r\nassert isinstance(interventional.masker, shap.maskers.Independent)\r\n\r\nconditional = shap.explainers.Linear(model, X, feature_perturbation=\"correlation_dependent\")\r\n\r\n# assertion fails\r\nassert isinstance(conditional.masker, shap.maskers.Impute)\r\n\r\n# assertion passes unexpectedly\r\nassert isinstance(conditional.masker, shap.maskers.Independent)\r\n```",
